column5: One of my better weeks fishing including my personal best.  Versatility was the key as roe, pinkies, beads, and hardware all produced at different times.
You can tell just how awesome it was in the first photo, congrats on the new PB man!
Congrats on a PB, a few tanks there.
That first fish is s a slob.   And the camera work makes it look like a 30 lber lol
nice fish, the hen aint no slouch either
you must have had a Bass guy takin the pics, they always seem to have a knack for making 2 pound smallies  look like 5 pounders
Congrats on the PB! Well done  Is that a St Croix wild river rod that you're tossing the skunk Kwikfish with? I'm definitely in the market for a new hardware stick.

Congrats on the PB! Well done  Is that a St Croix wild river rod that you're tossing the skunk Kwikfish with? I'm definitely in the market for a new hardware stick.  Thanks very much. Wow that's a good eye you have.  Yes it's a 10'6" St.Croix Wild River rod.  I got it 2-3 years ago and it's been absolutely great for me.  Exclusively use it for hardware.  The water that day was still a little dirty but cleaning up and I was using a frog pattern flatfish for 20 min with no luck.  I had read an article recently how black works better in dirty water as it provides more of a visible silhouette for the fish and sure enough the first cast connected. I was by myself for 1st, 2nd, and 4th pics so all I had was a go pro on a 6" tripod, hence the "bass" holds LOL.
Way to Matt.  I'll let Nooch know of our success.  Cheers, Ron...
